<TITLE> Mourners pay last respects to playwright Selim </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 16 (bdnews24.com)The coffin of Selim Al Din was taken to the Central Shahid Minar Wednesday morning to allow people from all walks of life to pay last respects to the distinguished playwright. Thousands of mourners, including teachers, students, poets, literati, artists, politicians and the public, paid solemn tribute to the deceased. The playwright was carried to the Shahid Minar, from BIRDEM via the National Museum, at around 10 am. Over a thousand people from the world of drama and theatre formed a silent procession ahead of the ambulance bearing the coffin from the National Museum compound. The coffin was placed on a special platform at the Minar, where it will remain till 1 pm. At 1.30 pm, Selim's namaz-e-janaza will be held at Dhaka University mosque. A second congregation will be held at Jahangirnagar University before the burial there. The renowned playwright and teacher died on Jan 14 after suffering a number of health complications including diabetes and cardiac failure. Among those present at the Shahid Minar in the morning were the late poet-playwright's wife Meherunnesa Selim, his brother and other relatives, as well as poet Syed Shamsul Haque, DU and JU teachers, students of theatre, music and drama, and representatives from a host of cultural and social organisations. Also paying last respects were adviser Rasheda K Chowdhury, Bangladesh Workers' Party president Rashed Khan Menon, Awami League presidium member, Bangladesh Communist Party members, freedom fighters and members of the public. A citizens' commemorative meeting will be held for Selim Al-Din at the Shahid Minar on Jan 21. bdnews24.
